%N A394837 Decimal expansion of the mean distance between two points chosen independently and uniformly at random from the interior of a unit square, one from each of the two sides of a given diagonal.
%H A394837 Artemas Martin, <a href="https://archive.org/details/mathematicalvis00martgoog/page/n59/mode/1up">Problem 20</a>, The Mathematical Visitor, Vol. 1, No. 2 (1878), pp. 41-42.
